  "text": "(ii) As mentioned above, in the planetary problem, µ measures the mass ratio between the planets and the star, while is related to the eccentricities and inclinations of the (instantaneous) two-body systems planet-star. Condition (9) is much weaker than Arnold's condition [CITATION_1] and allows, at least in principle, applications to a wider class of planetary systems. Clearly, in order to apply properly-degenerate KAM theory to a concrete system such as the outer Solar system 6 one should also estimate * in (9), which would be quite a technical achievement 7 .",
